news.news: Harris closed Friday's 98-94 win over Charlotte with 24 points (9-16 FG, 4-5 3Pt, 2-2 FT), 10 rebounds, one assist, one block and three steals across 36 minutes.
news.analysis: Harris fared well on both ends of the floor in Friday's outing, leading all Detroit players in scoring and threes made while swiping a team-high steals total and concluding as one of two players with a double-digit rebound mark in a double-double. Harris tallied his third double-double of the season while recording his first game with at least 20 points and 10 boards. He also matched a season-best steals mark, a feat he has also recorded on two other occasions.
